### [Proverbs Chapter 24](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 24:1](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">pro 24:1</span></span>

(Pro. 24:1-34)

(Compare [Pro 23:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro023.htm#003.md), [Pro
23:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro023.htm#017.md); [Psa
37:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa037.htm#001).md).

[Proverbs 24:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 24:2</span></span>

studieth--meditateth.

talk . . . mischief--Their expressed purposes are to do evil.

[Proverbs 24:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">pro 24:3</span></span>

(Compare [Pro 14:1](../../../bib/kjv/pro014.htm#001.md); [Isa
54:14](../../../bib/kjv/isa054.htm#014).md).

house--including the family.

[Proverbs 24:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 24:4</span></span>

by knowledge . . . riches-- ([Pro
8:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro008.htm#018.md); [Pro
21:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro021.htm#020).md).

[Proverbs 24:5](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">pro 24:5</span></span>

The general statement ([Ecc 9:16](../../../bib/kjv/ecc009.htm#016.md), [Ecc
9:18](../../../bib/kjv/ecc009.htm#018).md) is specially illustrated
(compare [Pro 21:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro021.htm#022.md); [Psa
144:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa144.htm#001).md).

[Proverbs 24:7](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">pro 24:7</span></span>

(Compare [Pro 14:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro014.htm#016).md).

in the gate--(Compare [Pro 22:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro022.htm#022).md).

[Proverbs 24:8](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">pro 24:8</span></span>

So called even if he fails to do evil.

[Proverbs 24:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">pro 24:9</span></span>

Same thought varied.

[Proverbs 24:10](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">pro 24:10</span></span>

Literally, "If thou fail in the day of straits (adversity), strait (or,
small) is thy strength," which is then truly tested.

[Proverbs 24:11](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">pro 24:11</span></span>

Neglect of known duty is sin ([Jam
4:17](../../../bib/kjv/jam004.htm#017).md).

ready--literally, "bowing down"

to be slain--that is, unjustly. God's retributive justice cannot be
avoided by professed ignorance.

[Proverbs 24:13](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">pro 24:13</span></span>

As delicious food whets the appetite, so should the rewards of wisdom
excite us to seek it.

[Proverbs 24:14](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">pro 24:14</span></span>

reward--literally, "after part," the proper result (compare [Pro
23:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro023.htm#018.md); [Psa
37:37-38](../../../bib/kjv/psa037.htm#037).md).

[Proverbs 24:15](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">pro 24:15</span></span>

The plots of the wicked against the good, though partially, shall not be
fully successful ([Psa 37:24](../../../bib/kjv/psa037.htm#024).md); while
the wicked, falling under penal evil, find no help.

[Proverbs 24:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">pro 24:16</span></span>

seven times--often, or many ([Pro
6:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro006.htm#016.md), [Pro
6:31](../../../bib/kjv/pro006.htm#031.md); [Pro
9:1](../../../bib/kjv/pro009.htm#001).md).

[Proverbs 24:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">pro 24:17</span></span>

Yet let none rejoice over the fate of evildoers, lest God punish their
wrong spirit by relieving the sufferer (compare [Pro
17:5](../../../bib/kjv/pro017.htm#005.md); [Job
31:29](../../../bib/kjv/job031.htm#029).md).

[Proverbs 24:19](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">pro 24:19</span></span>

([Psa 37:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa037.htm#001.md), [Psa
37:38](../../../bib/kjv/psa037.htm#038.md); [Psa
18:28](../../../bib/kjv/psa018.htm#028).md).

[Proverbs 24:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 24:20</span></span>

candle--or, "prosperity"; it shall come to an end ([Pro
13:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro013.htm#009.md); [Pro
20:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro020.htm#020).md).

[Proverbs 24:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 24:21</span></span>

A warning against impiety and resistance to lawful rule ([Rom
13:1-7](../../../bib/kjv/rom013.htm#001.md); [Pe1
2:17](../../../bib/kjv/pe1002.htm#017).md).

meddle . . . change--(Compare Margin), literally, "mingle not yourself,"
avoid the society of restless persons.

[Proverbs 24:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 24:22</span></span>

their calamity, &c.--either what God and the king inflict, or what
changers and their company suffer; better the first.

[Proverbs 24:23](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#023.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_023">pro 24:23</span></span>

These . . . wise--literally, "are of the wise," as authors (compare
"Psalms of David," Hebrew). "These" refers to the verses following, [Pro
24:24-34](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#024.md).

to have respect--literally, "to discern faces," show partiality,

[Proverbs 24:24](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#024.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_024">pro 24:24</span></span>

of which an example is justifying the wicked, to which is opposed,
rebuking him, which has a blessing.

[Proverbs 24:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 24:26</span></span>

kiss his lips--love and obey, do homage ([Psa
2:12](../../../bib/kjv/psa002.htm#012.md); [Sol
8:1](../../../bib/kjv/sol008.htm#001).md).

right answer--literally, "plain words" (compare [Pro
8:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro008.htm#009).md), opposed to deceptive, or
obscure.

[Proverbs 24:27](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#027.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_027">pro 24:27</span></span>

Prepare . . . in the field--Secure, by diligence, a proper support, and
then build; provide necessaries, then comforts, to which a house rather
pertained, in a mild climate, permitting the use of tents.

[Proverbs 24:28](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#028.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_028">pro 24:28</span></span>

Do not speak even truth needlessly against any, and never falsehood.

[Proverbs 24:29](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#029.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_029">pro 24:29</span></span>

Especially avoid retaliation ([Mat
5:43-45](../../../bib/kjv/mat005.htm#043.md); [Rom
12:17](../../../bib/kjv/rom012.htm#017).md).

[Proverbs 24:30](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#030.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_030">pro 24:30</span></span>

A striking picture of the effects of sloth.

[Proverbs 24:32](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#032.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_032">pro 24:32</span></span>

From the folly of the sluggard learn wisdom ([Pro
6:10-11](../../../bib/kjv/pro006.htm#010).md).

